The paper discusses the design challenges in next-generation wireless systems, which are related to information theory and communication (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The focus is on energy efficiency, which is a key concern in system design and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also considers the impact of channel fading, which is a common issue in wireless communication (cs.AR). Finally, the paper provides practical design guidelines, which are relevant to network implementation and engineering (cs.NI).
